%N A370888 a(n) = (n-1)*(2*(n-2)!+1).
%C A370888 The maximum deck size to perform the n-card trick using the Fitch Cheney method. This trick is known as the 5-card trick, where the maximum deck size is 52.
%C A370888 The method was later improved to serve a bigger deck described by A030495. In particular, the 5-card trick can be performed with the deck of size 124, and this size is the largest possible.
%C A370888 a(n) = A275929(n)-2.
%D A370888 Wallace Lee, Math Miracles, published by Seeman Printery, Durham, N.C., 1950.
